<b>What causes infections?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Infections can be caused by the following organisms:</span>

<b>Bacteria: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">They can be responsible for ailments such as tuberculosis, strep throat, and urinary tract infections.</span>

<b>Virus: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">They can cause different types of diseases ranging from mild to severe. For example, from fever to AIDS.</span>

<b>Fungi: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Majority of skin diseases like ringworms are caused by fungi. In fact, some types of fungi can infect the lung and brain.</span>

<b>Direct contact: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">The simplest way to get infected is by coming in physical contact with an infected person.</span>

